1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e5 Ng8!? { Surprise! Black undevelops the knight with the intention to re-route it to f5 where it can help apply maximum pressure against white's d4-pawn } (4... Nfd7 { The traditional mainline with lots of theory }) 5. f4 (5. Nf3 c5 6. dxc5 Bxc5 7. Bd3 Nc6 8. O-O a6 { It's important to play a6 before Nge7 in order to meet Na4 with Ba7. } (8... Nge7? 9. Na4!) 9. Bf4 Nge7 { [%csl Rf4,Rf3,Re5][%cal Gc8d7,Gd8c7,Gh7h6,Gg7g5,Ge7g6,Gh8g8,Ge8c8] }) 5... c5 6. Nf3 Nh6 7. Be3 Nf5 8. Bf2 cxd4 9. Nxd4 Nxd4 10. Bxd4 Nc6 11. Bf2 Bb4 12. a3 Bxc3+ 13. bxc3 Qa5 14. Qd2 b6 { [%csl Ga6,Rc2,Rc3][%cal Gc8a6,Ga8c8,Gc8c2,Ge8g8] } *


