1. e4 e6 2. d3 d5 3. Nd2 e5!? { looks weird at first, but black can get away with it! } 4. exd5 (4. Ngf3 Nc6 5. g3 Nf6 { This is a reverse philidor -- black has fluid development and can get an active position }) 4... Qxd5 5. c4?! Qd8 { [%csl Rd3,Rd4][%cal Gf8c5,Gb8c6,Gg8f6,Gc8f5] } *


