1. e4 e6 2. c4 (2. b3 { Horowitz Attack (popularized by GothamChess } 2... d5 3. Bb2 Nf6 { not letting white have any fun by accepting the gambit! } 4. e5 (4. Nc3? { loses a pawn } 4... d4 5. Nce2 Nxe4) 4... Ng8 { [%cal Gg8h6,Gh6f5,Gc7c5,Gb8c6,Gh7h5] }) (2. Nf3 d5 3. e5 Bd7 { by not playing c5, black can fully avoid the wing gambit and likely transpose into similar lines shown in chapter 3 } (3... c5 4. b4)) 2... d5 3. cxd5 exd5 4. Qb3 { Orthoschnapp Gambit } 4... dxe4 5. Bc4 Qe7 6. Nc3 Nd7! { Simply preparing Nc5 to harass the white queen } { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gd7c5] } 7. Nd5 Qe5 $17 { [%csl Gc7,Gc5][%cal Ge5c7,Gd7c5] } *


